# Homelab Repository — Agent Rules
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These rules apply to ALL AI agents (Cursor, GitHub Copilot, etc.) working
# in this repository. Follow them strictly to avoid mistakes and wasted cycles.

## INVESTIGATION STANDARD

You must reach ≥90% confidence before concluding any fact.
- Do NOT guess at hardware specs, Kubernetes versions, IP addresses, or config values.
- If you are less than 90% confident, keep digging: read more files, run commands, check docs.
- "I think it might be..." or "this could be..." are not acceptable unless you have exhausted your search.
- Always state your confidence level when delivering technical conclusions.

## ALWAYS DO YOUR RESEARCH

Before making ANY claim about:
- Hardware specifications (NIC speeds, CPU specs, RAM type, board model, drive sizes)
- Kubernetes/Talos/Cilium/ArgoCD API fields and supported versions
- AT&T BGW320 gateway capabilities
- Networking (NAT traversal, bonding, LACP, link aggregation)
- Tailscale behavior (DERP vs direct, port requirements)

...you MUST look it up. Read the actual file, run the command, or check the official docs URL.
NEVER assume from memory. Hardware in this homelab has been wrong in agent responses before.

## CLUSTER TOPOLOGY — KNOW THIS COLD

```
AT&T BGW320 (192.168.1.1, 5 GbE + 3x 1GbE)
    |
Minisforum M2 (192.168.1.10) — Talos v1.13.2, K8s v1.36.0
    - 2x 2.5 GbE ports (enp44s0 used for LB-IPAM)
    - 32 GB DDR5-4800 SINGLE-CHANNEL (1x SO-DIMM)
    - Intel Core Ultra 7 356H (16C)
    - Cilium v1.19.4 CNI + LB-IPAM pool 192.168.1.11-20
    - Longhorn v1.11.2 (default StorageClass)
    - ArgoCD v3.4.2 (192.168.1.14)
    - cert-manager v1.20.2 (homelab-ca ClusterIssuer, ECDSA P-256)
    - 3x vCluster: vc-prod, vc-dev, vc-staging
    |
GPU Node (192.168.1.101) — CURRENTLY Debian 12, pending Talos
    - ASUS PRIME Z390-P (not Z390-A — verify before writing)
    - Intel i9-9900K (8C/16T, 5.0 GHz boost)
    - 2x 16 GB Team Group DDR4 @ XMP 3200MHz (dual-channel)
    - NVIDIA RTX 3080 Ti (GA102, 12 GB GDDR6X)
    - NIC: Intel I219-V = 1 GbE ONLY
```

